 <!-- What does LP33 mean? -->
 <section class="mb-10">
 <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
 <h2 class="section-h2">
 What does life path number 33 mean?
 </h2>
 <div class="space-y-4 text-muted-text leading-relaxed">
 <p>
 Life path 33 is called the master teacher. The more you understand numerology, the more apt that name becomes. Number 33 is uncommon. It requires a very specific combination of birth date components. But beyond the arithmetic, 33 represents the highest expression of love and compassion available in the chart.
 </p>
 <p>
 Where LP11 is the master of intuition and LP22 is the master builder, LP33 is the master of unconditional service. The purpose in life is to nurture, heal, teach, and love without condition. If that sounds like a lot to carry, it is. LP33 isn't just caring. They're here to carry a specific karmic weight and transmute it into something that benefits others. That orientation toward service is embedded in the number itself.
 </p>
 <p>
 LP33 is rooted in number 6, the nurturer, but amplified to a different register. They don't just love family and community. They extend genuine compassion to strangers, to people who have wronged them, to humanity as a whole. Altruism isn't a practice for LP33. It's baseline. That's a calling.
 </p>
 <p>
 The challenge of LP33 is carrying this capacity without being destroyed by it. The sensitivity is real, empathy is real, others' suffering lands with weight. LP33s who haven't built structure around their giving, who haven't learned to receive and protect as well as give, often burn out and accumulate quiet anger at giving everything and having it taken for granted.
 </p>
 <div class="card-light p-5 mt-6">
 <p class="text-sm text-body-text"><span class="font-semibold">Note on master numbers:</span> LP33 also resonates with LP6 energy, since 3+3=6. Many LP33s operate closer to LP6 in early life and grow into the full 33 expression gradually. If LP33 fully resonates, read this page. If you're uncertain, <a href="/learn/life-path-number-6/" class="text-violet hover:underline">the LP6 page</a> may add useful context.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Traits image + personality -->
 <section class="py-16 px-4">
 <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
 <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-center">
 <div>
 <div class="mb-8 rounded-lg overflow-hidden border border-border/60 shadow-lg">
 <img
 src="/images/learn/Life Path Number 33 - Traits.webp"
 alt="Life Path 33 - The Master Teacher personality traits"
 class="w-full h-64 object-cover"
 />
 </div>
 </div>
 <div>
 <h2 class="section-h2">
 Personality traits of life path 33s
 </h2>
 <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
 LP33 individuals have a quality that's hard to name but easy to feel. There's warmth in their presence that isn't performed-genuine interest in the person in front of them, a quality of attention that makes people feel seen. This is the master healer's energy at work: consciousness so oriented toward the other that it's immediately felt.
 </p>
 <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
 LP33 has a depth of empathy that goes beyond understanding how someone feels to actually experiencing it. It's a gift and a challenge. LP33's emotional intelligence runs deep, but they absorb what others carry in ways that are hard to separate from their own state.
 </p>
 <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed">
 LP33 is also wise, underneath the warmth and compassion. Their knowledge of human nature, its needs, its fears, its capacity for growth comes from lived experience, natural attunement, and the synthesized wisdom of all numbers before 33. When they speak from this place, what they say cuts through in ways pure intelligence alone doesn't.
 </p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Strengths & challenges -->
 <section style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
 <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
 <h2 class="section-h2">Strengths &amp; challenges</h2>
 <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
 <div>
