 <!-- Love & Relationships -->
 <section class="py-16 px-4">
 <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
 <h2 class="section-h2">
 Life path 33 in love &amp; relationships
 </h2>
 <div class="space-y-4 text-muted-text leading-relaxed">
 <p>
 LP33 in love is all in. When they choose someone, they choose completely, with a depth of devotion and attentiveness partners describe as unlike anything they've experienced. LP33 doesn't love halfway. The master teacher's love is total.
 </p>
 <p>
 The challenge is LP33's love can tip into self-erasure. Their instinct to nurture means they subordinate their own needs, which produces resentment or dynamics where the partner takes without noticing. The work is learning to state what they need before the need becomes urgent.
 </p>
 <p>
 LP33's compatibility is strongest with partners who match their depth and give back generously. LP6 is often the most natural match: equally devoted, equally oriented toward care and home, capable of sustained attention. LP2 brings emotional intelligence and harmony that aligns with LP33's frequency. LP9 shares their orientation toward service and universal love in a way that creates genuine understanding.
 </p>
 <p>
 LP11 and LP22 both offer profound partnerships. The full master number tier resonates with LP33 in ways other numbers rarely reach. LP11's spiritual awareness and LP22's structural capability complement LP33's compassion and create partnerships that extend beyond the personal into shared purpose.
 </p>
 <p>
 What LP33 most needs is a partner who sees them as a person-not a healer, not a source of unconditional love, not a safe harbor. Someone curious about LP33's inner life, who asks about their experience, who notices when they're carrying too much. That partner is rare. But LP33 is worth waiting for.
 </p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

